cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

This paper deals with querying text using regular expressions and aggregate functions, which are common topics in database systems (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of Relational Algebra also suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The analysis of computational complexity is a fundamental aspect of theoretical computer science (cs.LG), and the use of approximative computation is also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
